ath>. From the figure and again using the small angle approximation, we can write
    
    <math xmlns:q="http://cnx.rice.edu/qml/1.0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:md="http://cnx.rice.edu/mdml" xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mtext>sin</mtext><mrow><mrow><mspace width="0.25em"/><mi>α</mi><mo stretchy="false">=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>D</mi><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac></mrow><mo stretchy="false">=</mo><mfrac><mi>D</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mrow></mrow><mrow><mtext>.</mtext></mrow></mrow><mrow/></mrow><annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12&#123;&quot;sin&quot;α= &#123;  &#123; &#123;D&#125; slash &#123;2&#125; &#125;  over  &#123;d&#125; &#125; = &#123;  &#123;D&#125;  over  &#123;2d&#125; &#125; &#125; &#123;&#125;</annotation></semantics></math>
    
    The <math xmlns:q="http://cnx.rice.edu/qml/1.0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:md="http://cnx.rice.edu/mdml" xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mtext fontstyle="italic">NA</mtext></mrow></mrow><mrow/></mrow></semantics></math> for a lens is <math xmlns:q="http://cnx.rice.edu/qml/1.0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:md="http://cnx.rice.edu/mdml" xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mtext fontstyle="italic">NA</mtext></mrow><mo stretchy="false">=</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow><mspace width="0.25em"/><mtext>sin</mtext><mspace width="0.25em"/><mi>α</mi></mrow></mrow><mrow/></mrow><annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12&#123; ital &quot;NA&quot;=n`&quot;sin&quot;α&#125; &#123;&#125;</annotation></semantics></math>, where <math xmlns:q="http://cnx.rice.edu/qml/1.0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:md="http://cnx.rice.edu/mdml" xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow/></mrow><annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12&#123;n&#125; &#123;&#125;</annotation></semantics></math> is the index of refraction of the medium between the objective lens and the object at point P.
    
